.TH "set_controller_speed" 9 "set_controller_speed" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
set_controller_speed \- set the frequency and/or mode of a specific controller segment.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" set_controller_speed
.BI "(struct controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "u8 adapter_speed "  ","
.BI "u8 hp_slot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
controller to change frequency/mode for.
.IP "adapter_speed" 12
the speed of the adapter we want to match.
.IP "hp_slot" 12
the slot number where the adapter is installed.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if we successfully change frequency and/or mode to match the
adapter speed.
